\label{skew brace on structure group}
Let $(X, r)$ be a  non-degenerate bijective solution to the Yang--Baxter equation and $G(X, r)$ its structure group with group operation $\circ$. Then there is another group operation $\cdot$ on the set $G(X, r)$ and a group isomorphism $\varphi : \big(G(X, r), \cdot \big) \to A(X, r)$ with $\varphi(x) = x$ for all $x \in X$, such that $\big(G(X, r), \cdot, \circ \big)$ is a skew left brace, where 
\begin{equation}\label{bijective 1-cocycle inverse}
a \cdot b = a \circ \varphi^{-1} \big(\lambda_a^{-1}(\varphi(b)) \big)    
\end{equation}
for $a, b\in G(X, r)$.

\label{t1}
Let $(G, \cdot)$ be a group and $\lambda : (G, \cdot) \to \Aut(G, \cdot)$ a group homomorphism. Then $ H_{\lambda} = \{ (\lambda_a, a) \,\mid \, a \in G \}$ is a subgroup of $\Hol(G)$ if and only if
