\label{injectivity-dehn-eta}
The following statements are equivalent for any quandle $X$:
\begin{enumerate}
\item $X$ embeds in $\Conj(H)$ for some group $H$.
\item The natural map $i_X: X \to \Adj(X)$ is injective.
\item $X \cong \mathcal{D}(S^G)$ for some group $G$ and a generating set $S$ of $G$.
\end{enumerate}

\label{thm Lebed Vendramin}
The following statements are equivalent for a finite quandle $X$:
\begin{enumerate}
\item $\Adj(X)$ has no torsion.
\item $\Adj(X)$ is free abelian.
\item $\Adj(X)$ is abelian.
\end{enumerate}

