\label{QuandAlg}
The  \index{rack algebra}{\it rack algebra} $\mathbb{Z}\{X\}$ of a rack $X$ is defined to be the  quotient  of $\Omega(X)$ by the relations
\begin{eqnarray}
  \label{rack alg rel 1}\eta_{x*y,z}\eta_{x,y} & =&  \eta_{x*z,y*z}\eta_{x,z},\\
 \label{rack alg rel 2}\eta_{x*y,z}\xi_{x,y} & =&  \xi_{x*z,y*z}\eta_{y,z},\\
 \label{rack alg rel 3}\xi_{x*y,z}& =& \eta_{x*z,y*z} \xi_{x,z} + \xi_{x*z,y*z}\xi_{y,z}.
\end{eqnarray}
The  \index{quandle algebra}{\it quandle algebra} $\mathbb{Z}(X)$ of a quandle $X$ is defined to be the  quotient  of $\Omega(X)$ by the relations \eqref{rack alg rel 1}--\eqref{rack alg rel 3} together with the relation
\begin{eqnarray}
\label{quandle alg rel 1} \xi_{x,x} + \eta_{x,x} &=& 1.
\end{eqnarray}

